hi all, 
after i have update to react@16.0 and read this https://twitter.com/dan_abramov/status/843822280132190208
and this
https://github.com/facebook/react/issues/9214#issuecomment-287763538

i have create fiddle with example on CodeSandbox
https://codesandbox.io/s/0xryn12myn
i don`t understand why in not worked with hot reload when component inside hoc
when component is updated we have error

`
this.subscriptions.some is not a function
`

```jsx
const connect = (Composed, props = {}) => {
class Connect extends Component {
  ...
  getChildContext() {
    return {
      some: () => {
       // No one subscriptions after unmout
        this.subscriptions.some();
      },
      ...
    }
  }
  ....
};

return Connect;
}

import connect, { Child, GrandChild } from './connect';

@connect()
class App extends Component {

  render() {
    return (
      <div>
        <Child
          some={() => { console.log(1) }}
        >
          <GrandChild>
            GrandChild1234
          </GrandChild>
        </Child>
      </div>
    )
  }
}
```

but when i try use it without hoc, all okay
https://codesandbox.io/s/mzzr3k93vx

```jsx
class Connect extends Component {
  ...
  getChildContext() {
    return {
      some: () => {
       // No one subscriptions after unmout
        this.subscriptions.some();
      },
      ...
    }
  }
  ....
};

...
render() {
    return (
      <Connect>
        <Child
          some={() => { console.log(1) }}
        >
          <GrandChild>
            GrandChild1234
          </GrandChild>
        </Child>
      </Connect>
    )
  }
...
```

```jsx
class Child extends Component {
  ...
  componentWillMount() {
    console.log('Child WillMount');
    this.subscribe();
  }
  ....
  componentWillUnmount() {
    console.log('Child WillUnmount');
    this.unSubscribe();
  }
  ...
}

class GrandChild extends Component {

  componentDidMount() {
    this.context.some();
    console.log('Child DidMount');
  }
  ....
}
```

i have only one idea, put Connect component inside connect decorator, and in render return Composed inside Parent, work fine), i hope it`s not bug ðŸ˜Ž

```jsx
const connect = (Composed, props = {}) => {

  class Connect extends Component {
    ...
    render() {
      return this.props.children;
    }

  }

  return class extends Component {
    render() {
      return (
        <Parent>
          <Composed
            {...props}
            {...this.props}
            {...this.state}
          />
        </Parent>
      );
    }
  };
};
```
